metadata.name: Why Don't We Go Outside
metadata.description:
I stare at my screen when I wake up.
I stare at my screen when I eat.
I stare at my screen when I'm feeling horny.
I stare at my screen when I'm with my friends.
I stare at my screen when I'm watching movies on another screen.
I stare at my screen when there's war.
I stare at my screen when peace is achieved.
I stare at my screen when I'm working.
I stare at my screen when I'm free.
I stare at my screen even when my screen is off.

The screen became the needle.
The screen became the life.
And what is life without a screen? 
Or is it a screen without a life?
